headline: Robolink Launches Drone Coding in Classrooms — Directly from a Texas Instruments Graphing Calculator
summary: SAN DIEGO, August 21, 2025--Robolink, one of Inc. 5000’s fastest-growing private companies in 2025, today announced an exciting new collaboration with Texas Instruments (TI) Education Technology to bring future-ready learning to more classrooms across the country. This school year, students will be able to program Robolink’s award-winning CoDrone EDU using Python-capable TI-Nspire™ CX II graphing calculators.
